This module allows defining a domestic address format for each country, which will be
applied in printed reports when the transactions are domestic.

**Table of contents**

.. contents::
   :local:

Use Cases / Context
===================

Useful for applying different address layouts for domestic and international transactions.
For example, show the country name for international transactions but omit it for domestic ones.

Configuration
=============

- Enable developer mode, and go to *Contacts > Configuration > Countries*.
- Select a country associated with a company in your database.
- Fill in the Domestic Address Format.

